      "value": "<p><em>Biome: Underdark & Caves</em></p>\\n<p>A pale, fleshy fungus with a tough, rubbery texture, commonly found near carnivorous plants and on corpses. The cephalophage absorbs fragments of the dead's memories and personalityâ€”individual mushrooms have been found containing traces of up to ten different minds. Eating a cephalophage transfers those memories and quirks to the eater. The effects last [[/roll 1d4]] hours, during which the eater can access the absorbed memories. After the effect ends, the eater may still experience occasional flashbacks or personality instability; under intense stress or triggering situations, the eater must roll under their Intelligence modifier or be overwhelmed by another person's memories. Some faiths condemn the cephalophage as unholy, believing it prevents a soul from passing on and may contribute to undeath.</p>",
